<p>China has taken its dispute with Japan over Prime Minister Sanae Takaichi’s Taiwan remarks to the United Nations, with its UN envoy calling the comments “highly dangerous,” and its UN mission asserting a right of “self-defence” against any Japanese armed intervention in the cross-Strait situation [scmp.com#1][thehindu.com#1]. The spat has escalated into trade and diplomatic friction expected to affect businesses on both sides, and the United States reaffirmed “unshakeable” support for Japan [aljazeera.com#1][firstpost.com#2].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/92xsnmjyZF5fUccnGQsU7oScvXw0Hffl03kcYTQ7rDlNp6oQpWG8euq5OSnNNVfrMMMzndOUQryeZFTWsxyy0cJseBW4l-VI89eQi-nokSjGf6-O7ZrYtD5aLugQkNs2DMgnTb2EiX1H353FGI_cca9ORgI2cGokuVvmFLiwn6cILeewYA' alt='Japan’s Prime Minister Sanae Takaichi arrives for a meeting with China’s Xi Jinping in Gyeongju, South Korea, in October.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>UN escalation: China’s UN envoy Fu Cong wrote to Secretary-General António Guterres, calling Takaichi’s comments “highly dangerous” and saying Japan was “unrepentant,” as Beijing lodged its complaint at the UN [scmp.com#1].</li><li>Self-defence claim: China’s UN mission said any Japanese armed intervention in the cross-Strait situation would be an act of aggression and asserted China’s right of self-defence [thehindu.com#1].</li><li>Business fallout: The dispute has rapidly escalated into a trade and diplomatic confrontation set to affect businesses in both countries [aljazeera.com#1].</li><li>US stance: The United States reiterated its “unshakeable” support for Japan as tensions rose over Beijing’s objections [firstpost.com#2].</li><li>Political context: Takaichi’s remarks drew reprisals from Beijing, complicating her early efforts to manage ties with China [nytimes.com#1].</li></ul><blockquote>“If Japan dares to attempt an armed intervention in the cross-Strait situation, it would be an act of aggression.” - China’s U.N. mission (statement)</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>China (UN mission): Beijing says Takaichi’s remarks are “highly dangerous,” calls Japan “unrepentant,” and warns it would exercise self-defence if Japan attempted armed intervention across the Strait [scmp.com#1][thehindu.com#1]. (<a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/china/diplomacy/article/3333777/highly-dangerous-chinas-un-envoy-pours-fresh-scorn-unrepentant-takaichi'>SCMP; The Hindu</a>)</li><li>Japan (government of PM Sanae Takaichi): Takaichi faces pressure to avoid escalation with China without appearing weak domestically after her Taiwan-related remarks [nytimes.com#1]. (<a href='https://www.nytimes.com/2025/11/21/world/asia/japan-china-taiwan-dispute.html'>New York Times</a>)</li><li>United States: Washington reaffirmed its “unshakeable” support for Japan amid Beijing’s escalation over the Taiwan remarks [firstpost.com#2]. (<a href='https://www.firstpost.com/world/us-reaffirms-unshakeable-support-for-japan-as-china-escalates-over-taiwan-remarks-13952964.html'>Firstpost</a>)</li><li>Businesses in China and Japan: Companies on both sides are bracing for trade and diplomatic spillovers as the spat deepens [aljazeera.com#1]. (<a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/economy/2025/11/22/china-spat-with-japan-on-taiwan-deepens-reaches-un-whats-it-all-about'>Al Jazeera</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.reddit.com/r/worldnews/comments/1p3af32/japans_takaichi_rejects_china_demand_to_retract/'>Japan’s Takaichi Rejects China Demand to Retract Taiwan Remarks</a> - reddit.com</li><li><a href='https://www.nytimes.com/2025/11/21/world/asia/japan-china-taiwan-dispute.html'>Japan’s New Leader Mentions Taiwan, and Tanks Her Relationship With China</a> - nytimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/economy/2025/11/22/china-spat-with-japan-on-taiwan-deepens-reaches-un-whats-it-all-about'>China spat with Japan on Taiwan deepens, reaches UN: What’s it all about?</a> - aljazeera.com</li><li><a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/china-takes-spat-with-japan-over-taiwan-to-un-cites-right-of-self-defence-against-armed-intervention/article70310603.ece'>China takes spat with Japan over Taiwan to UN, cites right of ‘self-defence’ against armed intervention</a> - thehindu.com</li><li><a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/china/diplomacy/article/3333777/highly-dangerous-chinas-un-envoy-pours-fresh-scorn-unrepentant-takaichi'>China’s UN envoy pours fresh scorn on Japan’s ‘unrepentant’ Takaichi</a> - scmp.com</li><li><a href='https://www.firstpost.com/world/china-drags-japan-to-un-over-takaichis-remarks-on-taiwan-as-tensions-hit-new-low-13953071.html'>China drags Japan to UN over Takaichi’s remarks on Taiwan as tensions hit new low</a> - firstpost.com</li></ul>